00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:00,912
In this first scene

2
00:00:01,312 --> 00:00:04,375
we explore the basic structure of a JavaScript function

3
00:00:04,763 --> 00:00:09,725
A function in JavaScript is a block of code designed to perform a particular task

4
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:12,075
It can be reused with different inputs

5
00:00:12,463 --> 00:00:13,537
known as parameters

6
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,212
Functions are defined with the function keyword

7
00:00:16,575 --> 00:00:17,562
followed by a name

8
00:00:18,087 --> 00:00:19,337
and then parentheses

9
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:23,238
The code to be executed is placed inside curly brackets

10
00:00:23,712 --> 00:00:29,488
Understanding functions is essential because it helps in organizing code into reusable components

11
00:00:29,762 --> 00:00:31,938
making the code clean and manageable

